<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:my="http://example.com/my" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_ærdæg" xml:lang="os"><form type="lemma"><orth>ærdæg</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>половина</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>half</q></cit></sense><sense><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>сторона</q></cit><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>side</q></cit></sense></sense><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_ærdæg." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>Batraz... c ʼītījy ærdæg ratydta æmæ jæ jæ særyl cæværdta</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Батраз оторвал половину глетчера и положил себе на голову</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>Batraz tore a half of glacier and put it on his head</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 26</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>ræǵawæn je ʽrdæg mæn, innæ ʽrdæg—dæw</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>половина табуна моя, другая половина — твоя</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>one half of the herd is mine, the other is yours</q></cit></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>bæx ærdæg xwærd fæccæj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>лошадь была наполовину съедена</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the horse was half eaten</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>16%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><re><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><form type="lemma"><orth>ærdægmard</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>полумертвый</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>half dead</q></cit></sense></re><re><form type="lemma"><orth>ærdægax˳yr</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>полуученый</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>half learnt</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>недоучка</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>half-educated person</q></cit></sense></sense></re><cit type="exampleGroup" corresp="#sense_." n=""><cit type="example"><quote>Batraz... c ʼītījy ærdæg ratydta æmæ jæ jæ særyl cæværdta</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Батраз оторвал половину глетчера и положил себе на голову</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>Batraz tore a half of glacier and put it on his head</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_ОЭ"/><biblScope>I 26</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>ræǵawæn je ʽrdæg mæn, innæ ʽrdæg—dæw</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>половина табуна моя, другая половина — твоя</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>one half of the herd is mine, the other is yours</q></cit></cit><cit type="example" xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg type="dialect"><lang/></usg><quote>bæx ærdæg xwærd fæccæj</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>лошадь была наполовину съедена</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the horse was half eaten</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>16%l3%l</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>arda-</w><gloss><q>половина</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘сторона’ с обычным наращением -%ig%i (← *%iarda-ka%i-). Без наращения %iærd%i- со значением ‘сторона’ выступает во множестве производных и сложных слов: <xr><ref target="#entry_ardæm"/></xr> ‘сюда’, <xr><ref target="#entry_ūrdæm"/></xr> ‘туда’, <xr><ref target="#entry_alyrdæm"/></xr> ‘во все стороны’, <xr><ref target="#entry_fæjnærdæm"/></xr> ‘в разные стороны’, <xr><ref target="#entry_wælærdæm"/></xr> ‘вверх’, <xr><ref target="#entry_dælærdæm"/></xr> ‘вниз’, <xr><ref target="#entry_falærdæm"/></xr> ‘на ту сторону’, <xr><ref target="#entry_acyrdæm"/></xr> ‘на эту сторону’ и др.; ср. также <xr><ref target="#entry_ærdæbon"/></xr> ‘давеча’. Слово хорошо представлено в индоиранских языках: <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><w>*-ardak</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*-ard(ʼrδ)</w><gloss><q>сторона</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (%i*wīspard-%i = <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>alyrdæm</w><gloss><q>во все стороны</q></gloss></mentioned>, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>biśśi hālaa</w></mentioned> id.), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>hālaa</w></mentioned> (из *%iardaka%i), <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>alak</w></mentioned> (из *%iardak%i), <mentioned xml:lang="pal-x-turfan"><lang/><w>ʽārag</w></mentioned> (<bibl corresp=""/>%bМО XV 205)%b, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>arəδa-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>ardha-</w><gloss><q>половина</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘сторона’.— <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><lang/><w>ord</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>Umgebung</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kv"><w>ordö</w><gloss><q>zu</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><w>ordyn</w><gloss><q>bei</q></gloss></mentioned>,  etc. (<bibl corresp=""/>%bW i е d е m а n n. Syrjänisch-Deutsches Wörterbuch 209%b), возможно, усвоено из скифского. Более широкое распространение получило в других иранских языках синонимическое слово *%inaima%i-, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>aδara.naemat</w></mentioned> — <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>dælærdygæj</w><gloss><q>снизу</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>upara.nаеmat</w></mentioned> =<mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>wælærdygæj</w><gloss><q>сверху</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 77</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl corresp=""><biblScope>50</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/><w>arda-</w><gloss><q>half</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘side’ with a regular augmentation -%ig%i (← *%iarda-ka%i-). Without augmentation, %iærd%i- as ‘half’ is found in a number of derivates and complex words: <xr><ref target="#entry_ardæm"/></xr> 'hither’, <xr><ref target="#entry_ūrdæm"/></xr> ‘thither, <xr><ref target="#entry_alyrdæm"/></xr> ‘towards all directions’, <xr><ref target="#entry_fæjnærdæm"/></xr> ‘towards different directions’, <xr><ref target="#entry_wælærdæm"/></xr> ‘up’, <xr><ref target="#entry_dælærdæm"/></xr> ‘down’, <xr><ref target="#entry_falærdæm"/></xr> ‘on that side’, <xr><ref target="#entry_acyrdæm"/></xr> ‘on this side’ and others; compare also <xr><ref target="#entry_ærdæbon"/></xr> ‘recently’. The word is well presented in Indoiranian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="sog"><lang/><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><w>*-ardak</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sog"><w>*-ard(ʼrδ)</w><gloss><q>side</q></gloss></mentioned>,  (%i*wīspard-%i = <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>alyrdæm</w><gloss><q>towards all directions</q></gloss></mentioned>, compare <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>biśśi hālaa</w></mentioned> id.), <mentioned xml:lang="kho"><lang/><w>hālaa</w></mentioned> (from *%iardaka%i), <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/><w>alak</w></mentioned> (from *%iardak%i), <mentioned xml:lang="pal-x-turfan"><lang/><w>ʽārag</w></mentioned> (<bibl corresp=""/>%bМО XV 205)%b, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>arəδa-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/><w>ardha-</w><gloss><q>half</q></gloss></mentioned>, ‘side’.— <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><lang/><w>ord</w><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><note type="comment" xml:lang=""/><gloss><q>Umgebung</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kv"><w>ordö</w><gloss><q>zu</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="kv"><w>ordyn</w><gloss><q>bei</q></gloss></mentioned>,  etc. (<bibl corresp=""><biblScope>Syrjänisch-Deutsches Wörterbuch 209</biblScope></bibl>), possibly comes from Scythian. More widespread in other Iranian languages is the synonymous word *%inaima%i-, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>aδara.naemat</w></mentioned> — <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>dælærdygæj</w><gloss><q>underneath</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/><w>upara.nаеmat</w></mentioned> =<mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/><w>wælærdygæj</w><gloss><q>above</q></gloss></mentioned>.%n<bibl corresp="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"><biblScope>II 77</biblScope></bibl>; <bibl corresp=""><biblScope>50</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>